<FIRST>u i AM-Romania-Communique     12-22 0101</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Romania-Communique,0107</SECOND>
<HEAD>Excerpts From Communique on Proposals For Future Government</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Romania, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUCHAREST, Romania (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Excerpts from a communique read on
Romanian TV on Friday night by a member of the National Salvation
Committee, the temporary government, on planned reforms:
   _ Free elections by April.
   _ Commitment to a pluralistic society.
   _ Continued membership in the Warsaw Pact.
   _ Commitment to the idea of a ``common European home.''
   _ Abolishment of all structures of the Ceausescu dictatorship.
   _ Placement of the army under the control of the civil
government, and placement of the security apparatus under the army.
</TEXT>
