<HEAD>33 Killed In Two South Africa Bus Accidents</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus carrying gold miners
home for the holidays overturned, and another bus caught fire while
most of its passengers slept, police said Saturday. At least 33
people died in the incidents.
   Twenty-two people died in the fire, which broke out Friday night
on a bus that stopped along a highway near the central city of
Bloemfontein because of mechanical problems. The bus carried 95
passengers.
   Eleven men were killed and 20 injured when a bus carrying miners
to the black homeland of Transkei overturned in southern Natal
province, police said.
